<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Tunset Rhyzing</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-19 16:08:43</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>OK - here is the deal on this bow.  It IS no drop as a previous poster said - but it is not dropped off a named mob.  When you enter the hole - there are a few elementals to kill down a main hallway.  After you clear the hallway, you go down some stairs which lead to a small hallway with a skeleton in it.  DO NOT ATTACK THE SKELETON.  This is a bug and he is a pet of something that you dont wanna meet.  He wont attack you if you leave him alone.  Anyway, at the end of this hallway where the skelli is, there are 2 more elementals and one roamer.  Once you have killed these, you can move down the now larger hall to where it opens to the left.  Take your time and sit on the rock to med up.  In the distance - you will see a rock golem (lvl 50-52) and a elemental crusader (also kinda nasty, but you will have encountered a few on the way down).  The bow drops off the golem.  It is not named, and may I STONGLY suggest an enchanter for your trip or you will find yourself on a CR quite quickly.  Anyway, I love mine and its well worth the trip down there to get it.  Once you have killed the golem and the cru, you can proceed back to the top for almost an immediate repop and do it all again until you get the bow - also very nice xp.<BR>
<BR>
Tunset Rhyzing<BR>
Champion of the 51st<BR>
Brothers of the Moo<BR>
Quellious</font></td></tr></table>
